    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Pteris pectiniformis are fever, caused by its antipyretic properties, which reduce body temperature by increasing perspiration and heat loss. Skin conditions like eczema and dermatitis are treated with Pteris pectiniformis due to its anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects, which soothe and calm irritated skin. Pteris pectiniformis also exhibits antiviral properties, which aid in the treatment of viral infections such as herpes and shingles. Additionally, this plant has been used to treat gastrointestinal disorders like diarrhea and dysentery due to its antidiarrheal and antibacterial properties. Respiratory problems like bronchitis and asthma are alleviated by Pteris pectiniformis due to its expectorant and bronchodilator effects.",
