    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Pteris pectiniformis are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial. Antimicrobial properties of Pteris pectiniformis have been attributed to flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils that inhibit the growth of various pathogenic microorganisms. Antioxidant activity of this plant has been associated with the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Additionally, Pteris pectiniformis exhibits anti-inflammatory activity, particularly due to the presence of saponins and flavonoids, which modulate the immune response and reduce inflammation. Furthermore, the bioactive compounds present in Pteris pectiniformis, including flavonoids and phenolic acids, have been found to exhibit hepatoprotective and cardioprotective effects.",
