    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Pteris pectiniformis are flavonoids, terpenoids, saponins, and phenolic acids. Flavonoids such as isoorientin and its 3-O-glucoside have been identified as the main flavonoid components, exhibiting antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. Terpenoids like pterosin B have shown antimicrobial properties, while saponins have been reported to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects. Phenolic acids like ferulic acid have been found to exhibit antioxidant activity and protect against lipid peroxidation. The antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties of these constituents contribute to the plant's potential healing effects.",
