    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Pteris pectiniformis are infusion made by steeping the leaves in hot water to treat fever and rheumatism, tea prepared similarly for digestive issues and as a diuretic, tincture by soaking the leaves in a solvent to treat skin conditions and inflammation, decoction made by boiling the roots to treat respiratory issues, and salve by mixing the leaves with a carrier oil to treat wounds and skin irritations. The infusion is rich in flavonoids and phenolic acids that exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. The tea is used to relieve symptoms of irritable bowel syndrome and other gastrointestinal disorders due to its prebiotic properties. The tincture is effective in treating skin conditions such as eczema and acne due to its anti-inflammatory and antibacterial properties. The decoction and salve are used to treat respiratory issues and skin irritations due to their anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities.",
